      "text": [
        " : «إِنَّ سُلَيْمَانَ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ قَدْ حَجَّ اَلْبَيْتَ فِي اَلْجِنِّ وَ اَلْإِنْسِ وَ اَلطَّيْرِ وَ اَلرِّيَاحِ وَ كَسَا اَلْبَيْتَ اَلْقَبَاطِيَّ »."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2285 - Zurara narrated from Abu Ja'far (as), who said:\n\"Indeed, Sulayman (as) performed Hajj to the House with the jinn, humans, birds, and winds, and he clothed the Kaaba with garments of fine Egyptian linen (Qibatiyya).\""
        ]
      }
